04/07/2003
MOSCOW, Russia -- Romanian President Ion Iliescu said on Thursday (3 July) that relations with Russia should improve significantly when the two countries sign a friendship agreement Friday. The deal took ten years to negotiate. Iliescu said he hopes the agreement would boost economic ties with Russia. Trade now stands at $1.3 billion, compared to over $5 billion before 1989.
In other news, Iliescu clarified remarks he made in an interview with the Russian daily <I>Nezavisimaya Gazeta</I>. He denied suggesting that the former Soviet republic of Moldova should one day be reunited with neighbouring Romania. (Mediafax, Rompres - 04/07/03; AFP - 03/07/03)
